Item: Developments on health privacy…
<http://www.lightbluetouchpaper.org/2006/11/27/developments-on-health-privacy/>
Date: 2006-11-27 23:08:23 UTC
The Register[1] reports a leaked document[2] from the NHS which concludes that sensitive patient records would probably be safer held locally, rather than stored on a national database as the Government proposes.

This follows a poll last week in which a majority of GPs[3] said they would not upload their patients’ records to the national database. Together the poll and the leak are a double whammy for the misguided and wasteful project to centralise all computer systems in the NHS[4].

On Wednesday we are launching a campaign[5] to persuade patients to opt out too. The inaugural meeting will be from 7 to 9 PM in Imperial College, London[6]. For background, see recent posts on opting out[7] and on kids’ databases[8].

